            <b>A thought for tomorrow: China=92s Corn Imports are Beginning
of =91New=20
            Era=92<br>
            </b>The chairman and chief consultant of Shanghai JC
Intelligence=20
            Co. Ltd. (JCI) said his organization anticipates that China
will import=20
            some 1.7 million tons of corn this year, 5.8 million tons
next year=20
            and as much as 15 million tons in 2014-2015.<br>
            <br>
            Speaking through a translator, JCI=92s Hanver Li told those at
the U.S.=20
            Grains Council=92s 50th Annual Board of Delegates Meeting that
demand=20
            for corn in China is simply outstripping the country=92s
production=20
            trend. China=92s economy continues to grow, he explained, which
is driving=20
            an increase in demand for meat, milk and eggs because as
incomes rise,=20
            food is one of the first items people look to buy.<br>
            (from USGC Global Update July 22, 2010)<br>
            See: <a
href=3D"http://www.grains.org/news-events/2544-jci-chinas-corn-imports-are-=
